yle="color:#ff0000; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">88% of people do not understand community transport; 62% how they can access it &amp; cost; 42%.routes</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24.26pt; padding-left:11.19pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Community Transport providers identified need for: strong identity branding, single booking system, use of concessionary bus passes, linkages with welsh scheme (medical trips where FOD residents are referred to Welsh outpatient clinics). (2011/12)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24.26pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Commissioners, such as NHS and 2gether Trust highlighted barriers using the four voluntary sector transport organisations. They identified a need for a single call that is quick, simple, consistent and reliable. (2011/12) </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Local / regional plans / strategies:</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">All</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of the following</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> highlight transport as one of the key issues which people feel needs improving.  </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94